---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Annual Doctoral Symposium 2026 | Doctoral College UK" description="Join DCUK's Annual Doctoral Symposium on 18–20 November 2026 — three days of research presentations, keynotes, and networking for doctoral researchers and supervisors.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Events 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Annual Doctoral Symposium 2026</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">18–20 November 2026 &mdash; Online &amp; London</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">Our annual celebration of doctoral research brings together researchers, supervisors, alumni, and guests for a day of intellectual exchange, peer learning, and community. Open to all DCUK researchers and invited guests.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Register Interest</a>
        <a href="#events" class="btn-outline">View all events</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the Symposium -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">About the Symposium</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">A Day for the DCUK Research Community</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The DCUK Annual Doctoral Symposium is the centrepiece of our academic year. It is a day for researchers at all stages — from those just beginning their doctoral journey to those preparing to submit — to share their work, receive peer feedback, and connect with the wider community of practitioner-scholars.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The 2026 Symposium runs in a hybrid format, with a live venue in London and a fully interactive online stream. Whether you attend in person or remotely, you will have access to the full programme, including keynotes, parallel research sessions, methods workshops, and an evening networking reception (in-person).</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Research presentations are supported and developmental — this is not a competitive conference but a community event. Feedback is constructive, facilitated by a faculty discussant, and designed to help researchers strengthen their work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Date</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">18–20 November 2026</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Format</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Hybrid — London venue (TBC) and fully interactive online stream</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Who Should Attend</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">All current DCUK researchers, alumni, supervisors, and invited professional guests. Applications to present welcome from Year 1 onwards.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Cost</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Free for all current DCUK researchers and supervisors. Guest tickets: £95 in-person, £25 online. Alumni: complimentary online access.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Abstracts</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Submission deadline for research presentations: 1 August 2026. 300-word abstract required. All submissions reviewed by the Symposium Committee.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Programme -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Symposium Day</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Provisional Programme — 18–20 November 2026</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">09:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Welcome and Opening Keynote</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Prof. Stanley Oliver, Director — DCUK. Annual research community address and keynote on practitioner research in a changing world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">10:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session A</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Parallel tracks: Management & Strategy / Education Leadership. Three presentations per track, each with faculty discussant feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">11:30</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Break &amp; Networking</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person coffee and discussion. Online researchers participate in facilitated virtual networking rooms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">12:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Methods Workshop</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Annual methods focus session. 2026 theme: <em>Research Ethics in Insider Research — navigating access, positionality, and organisational politics.</em></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">13:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Lunch</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">In-person lunch provided at the London venue. Online researchers take a 60-minute break.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">14:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Researcher Presentations — Session B</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Parallel tracks: Organisational Behaviour &amp; HR / Innovation &amp; Technology. Three presentations per track.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">15:30</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Alumni Keynote</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">A DCUK alumnus presents the impact of their doctoral research on practice. 2025 speaker: Dr. Maria Delacroix, Executive Director, NHS Greater London.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start border-b border-border pb-4">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">16:30</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Closing Plenary &amp; Community Discussion</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Reflections from the day, announcements, and open discussion on the future of practitioner research.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent w-20 flex-shrink-0 pt-1">18:00</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Evening Reception (In-Person)</h3>
            <p class="text-muted text-sm">Informal drinks and networking for in-person attendees at the London venue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- All Events -->
  <section id="events" class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">2026 Events Calendar</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">All Upcoming Events</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">20 May 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Supervisor Workshop</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">A dedicated professional development day for doctoral supervisors. Themes: supporting researchers through difficulties, use of AI tools in research supervision, and managing multi-supervisor relationships. Facilitated by Dr. Zahra Salimi and external guests.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Online (half-day, 09:00–13:00)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> DCUK supervisors and invited HE professionals<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free for DCUK supervisors / £75 external
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">10 June 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Research Methods Webinar</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Open to all DCUK researchers and the wider practitioner-research community. Topic: <em>Navigating the Literature Review — from systematic search to critical synthesis.</em> Hosted by Dr. Paul Oliver, Head of Research, with a Q&A session.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Online webinar (90 minutes, 17:30–19:00)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> Open to all<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-sm text-accent font-medium mb-1">18–20 November 2026</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Annual Doctoral Symposium</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">The flagship event of the DCUK year. A full day of researcher presentations, keynotes, a methods workshop, and networking. Hybrid format — London venue and online stream. Abstract submissions open from 1 June.</p>
          <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
            <span class="font-medium">Format:</span> Hybrid — London &amp; Online (full day)<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Audience:</span> Researchers, supervisors, alumni, guests<br/>
            <span class="font-medium">Cost:</span> Free for current researchers
          </div>
          <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary text-sm">Register interest</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Join the community</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Whether you are a current researcher, prospective applicant, alumni, or interested professional — DCUK events are open and welcoming. Register your interest to receive updates and invitations.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Register interest</a>
        <a href="/experience" class="btn-outline">Student experience</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
